Skittles has been waiting a whole year for someone to notice how special she is!
Skittles is incredibly sweet and friendly. Despite spending most of her time in a kennel, this beautiful snow white nugget always has a happy grin on her face. She comes to her door to greet anyone who stops by, hoping to go for a walk or just to say hello. Skittles is nervous in the loud shelter though, and we believe this gentle older gal will thrive in a loving home, where she can build her confidence and trust.

Merry Christmas and Happy Hanukkah! This week's happy adoption tale comes from Sharon who adopted Stanley a few weeks ago, just in time to spread the holiday cheer! â™¥ï¸ğŸ’šâ™¥ï¸ğŸ’š
Sharon writes: "Stanley (formerly known as Calvin) could not be a better dog. He was shy when I first met him and Jessica, a volunteer at the shelter, noticed that he didn't see very well. We hung out for a little bit and I didn't think we were bonding but then something clicked and he realized I should be his person. So I took him home with me that day. I cannot say enough about adopting a #senior pet. He's housebroken, he is great on leash, he knows commands, he loves all dogs, people, and kitty cats, and he could not be happier to have a home! His vision isn't great but it doesn't stop him from having a great time! The longer he's with me, the more secure he is knowing he has a permanent home and it's so wonderful to see. I feel like I won the dog lottery. I'm so incredibly grateful to have the opportunity to be this dog's mom."
.
Thank you Sharon for giving our little senior a warm and loving home! We are so happy to hear he's thriving in his forever home! ğŸ’—âœ¨ğŸ„
